# HLS Scripts Directory

## Modern v++ Workflow (Vitis 2025.2+)

The legacy `vitis_hls -f script.tcl` workflow is deprecated.
Use the `v++` compiler instead.

### Quick Build

```bash
# From hardware/hls directory:
./scripts/build_hls.sh --clean

# Or directly with v++:
v++ -c --mode hls \
    --part xc7z020clg400-1 \
    --work_dir ./hls_output \
    --hls.clock 10ns \
    --hls.syn.top snn_top_hls \
    --hls.syn.file "src/snn_top_hls.cpp" \
    --hls.flow_target vivado
```

### Files

- `build_hls.sh` - Main build script using v++ CLI
- `hls_config.cfg` - HLS configuration (optional)
- `snn_top_hls_vpp.cfg` - v++ configuration file
- `vpp_hls_config.cfg` - Alternative v++ config

### Build Options

```bash
./scripts/build_hls.sh --help
```

Options:
- `--clean` - Remove previous build
- `--clock 8ns` - Set clock period
- `--part xc7z020clg400-1` - Target FPGA
- `--verbose` - Show detailed output

### Output

After successful synthesis:
- IP Package: `hls_output/hls/impl/ip/`
- Reports: `hls_output/hls/syn/report/csynth.rpt`
- ZIP: `hls_output/snn_top_hls.zip`

### Integration with Vivado

Copy the generated IP to your project:
```bash
cp -r hls_output/hls/impl/ip ../ip_repo/snn_top_hls
```
